# 04) Get the `hello-word` container from the Docker Hub, where it's available.

# Getting an image from Docker Hub
# Docker Hub is the place where open Docker images are stored.
# What is image?: A Docker image is a file, comprised of multiple layers, used to execute code in a Docker container. When the Docker user runs an image, it becomes one or multiple instances of that container.

# An image is bascially an immutable template for creating a container.
# Docker Image is you get when you build docker file.
# Docker Container is you get when you runyour Docker image.
# We can get Docker image from docker hub by pulling an then run it to get container.

docker pull hello-world

# To check image:
# docker image ls
